# Server
PORT=8080
DATA_DIR=/data

# Consistent SQLite snapshots (PD-33). All optional — sensible defaults below.
# Snapshots land in BACKUP_DIR (default <DATA_DIR>/backups) so whatever ships the
# data volume off-box (Hyper Backup today) carries a WAL-consistent copy.
# BACKUP_CRON=0 3 * * *          # schedule (default 03:00 daily)
# BACKUP_RETAIN_DAYS=14          # prune snapshots older than N days
# BACKUP_DIR=/data/backups       # output dir
# BACKUP_EXTRA_DB_PATHS=         # comma-separated extra DBs to snapshot

# Set to 1 on prod: if agent_tickets is empty on boot (e.g. a fresh/wiped
# volume), self-seed the committed baseline from tickets.seed.json. No-op once
# the board has any tickets. Leave unset in dev.
SEED_ON_BOOT=1

# Agent Dashboard — GitHub write token. The board DB is authoritative (D-055/C6); the old
# label→board read sync and queued→issue write sync are RETIRED, so no read token is used
# by the server anymore. This remaining token powers only best-effort GitHub WRITES: closing
# a linked issue "not planned" on ticket archive (PD-207 A) and mirroring an ask_human reply
# onto a linked issue (PD-250). It is a no-op (logs a line) when unset, so a partial setup
# boots cleanly. The app container has normal outbound (default bridge), so no egress change.
#
# WRITE-scoped token (Issues: Read and write on the linked repos). A fine-grained PAT.
# GITHUB_WRITE_TOKEN=

# agent-worker (D-044, D-045): runs as a SEPARATE, egress-hardened container with its OWN
# env file — NOT this one (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY must stay out of the web process). See
# ops/agent-worker/agent-worker.env.example.

# Music Tracker — see Widgets/Music Tracker/PROJECT.md for details
DJ_LIBRARY_PATH=/library
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=
SPOTIFY_PLAYLIST_ID=
LIDARR_URL=http://nas.local:8686
